TY  - JOUR
T1  - A General Class of Holt-Winters Type Forecasting Models
AU  - Roberts, S. A.
Y1  - 1982/07/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.28.7.808
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.28.7.808
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 808
EP  - 820
VL  - 28
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper is concerned with the formulation of short-term forecasting models, and introduces a range of models of considerable importance. These are defined in terms of predictions and sensible updating mechanisms for estimates of quantities such as level, growth, and seasonality, and constitute generalizations of familiar (linear) exponential smoothing predictors. They are shown to be equivalent to particular ARIMA models, and generally these do not lie within that subset of the ARIMA class which forms the basis of the Box-Jenkins modelling approach. It is argued that the models of this paper have a reasoned structure, and are to be preferred to the Box-Jenkins models for most socio-economic applications.
AB  - This paper is concerned with the formulation of short-term forecasting models, and introduces a range of models of considerable importance. These are defined in terms of predictions and sensible updating mechanisms for estimates of quantities such as level, growth, and seasonality, and constitute generalizations of familiar (linear) exponential smoothing predictors. They are shown to be equivalent to particular ARIMA models, and generally these do not lie within that subset of the ARIMA class which forms the basis of the Box-Jenkins modelling approach. It is argued that the models of this paper have a reasoned structure, and are to be preferred to the Box-Jenkins models for most socio-economic applications.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.28.7.808
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.28.7.808
Y2  - 2024/03/28
