TY  - JOUR
T1  - Some New Results for the M/M/1 Queue
AU  - Pegden, Claude Dennis
AU  - Rosenshine, Matthew
Y1  - 1982/07/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.28.7.821
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.28.7.821
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 821
EP  - 828
VL  - 28
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - New results are obtained for the single server queue with Poisson arrivals and exponential service times. A closed form solution involving only finite sums is obtained for the probability that exactly i arrivals and j services occur over a time interval of length t in a queueing system that is idle at the beginning of the interval. Since many applications of queueing theory involve queues which are emptied and restarted periodically and thus not susceptible to analysis using the well-known equilibrium results, there are many potential applications for results obtained. Some ways in which the results obtained may be applied are discussed.
AB  - New results are obtained for the single server queue with Poisson arrivals and exponential service times. A closed form solution involving only finite sums is obtained for the probability that exactly i arrivals and j services occur over a time interval of length t in a queueing system that is idle at the beginning of the interval. Since many applications of queueing theory involve queues which are emptied and restarted periodically and thus not susceptible to analysis using the well-known equilibrium results, there are many potential applications for results obtained. Some ways in which the results obtained may be applied are discussed.
